Privacy Policy – FingerRoll

Effective Date: August 26, 2025

FingerRoll (“we”, “our”, or “us”) respects your privacy and is committed to protecting it. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information when you use our mobile application FingerRoll.

1. Information We Collect

FingerRoll is designed to work without requiring personal information. We may collect the following minimal data:

Device information: Type of device, operating system, app version (for app functionality and performance improvements).

Anonymous usage data: How you interact with the app, such as which features are used and session duration.

We do NOT collect:

Your name, email, phone number, or any sensitive personal data.

Location data.

2. How We Use Your Data

We use collected data only for:

Improving app performance and stability.

Enhancing user experience and fixing bugs.

Generating anonymized statistics for analytics purposes.

3. Third-Party Services

FingerRoll may use third-party analytics services (e.g., Google Analytics for Firebase) to understand app usage. These services:

Collect only anonymized or aggregated data.

Do not identify individual users personally.

We do not share your personal data with advertisers or marketers.

4. Data Security

We implement reasonable technical measures to protect your data against unauthorized access or misuse. However, no app or internet service is completely secure.

5. Children’s Privacy

FingerRoll does not target children under 13. If we become aware that personal information of a child has been collected, we will take steps to delete it.

6. Your Rights

You have the right to:

Request information about the data we collect.

Request deletion of any data associated with your device.

For inquiries, contact: privacy@fingerrollapp.com

7. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify users through app updates or the app itself.

By using FingerRoll, you agree to this Privacy Policy.
